io.smallrye.mutiny.groups

Class MultiConcat

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.smallrye.mutiny.groups.MultiConcat

  • public class MultiConcat
extends Object
    Creates new Multi by concatenating several Multi or Publisher. This class allows configuring how the concatenation is executed. Unlike a merge, a concatenation emits the items in order. Streams are read one-by-one and the items are emitted in this order.

      • collectFailures

        public MultiConcat collectFailures()
        Indicates the the concatenation process should not propagate the first receive failure, but collect them until all the items from all (non-failing) participants have ben emitted. Then, the failures are propagated downstream (as a CompositeException if several failures have been received).
        Returns:
        this MultiConcat configured to collect the failures.
